						               													<description>D&amp;eacute;finimages is a riddle and charade-like game, where players solve puzzles based on definitions and with 60 picture cards, which illustrate monosyllabic words.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Variant A:  The 60 picture cards are displayed so they can be seen by all the players.  Each round, a player is a appointed as &amp;quot;Game Master&amp;quot; and reads a definition; the first player to find the cards (2, 3 or 4) illustrating the syllables of the word defined wins the points of that turn.  After a round (10 definitions: 10 turns), an other player is Game Master for the next round; a game can have up to 10 rounds (of 10 turns).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Variant B:  The players agree on the number of cards (from 30 to 60) to be displayed and a time limit (or to not have a time limit).  The players try to make as many words as possible by picking the picture cards illustrating the syllables of a word.  All the players play concurrently.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In both variants, each word is worth the number of cards it required to illustrate the syllables of the word.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There's also a variant for children.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
